              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 intense neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 350 uA, 220 keV deuteron beam, and the neutron",
                "fluence rate was 1 E11n/s. The tritium-titanium (T-",
                "Ti) target was 2.18 mg/cm2 thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The well calibrated HPGE detector (ORTEC, made",
                "in USA) has a relative efficiency of ~68% and an",
                "energy resolution of 1.7 keV (FWHM) at 1.33 MeV. The",
                "uncertainty in the absolute efficiency curve at 5.5",
                "cm was estimated to be ~2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The samples (ThO2 powder of 99.5% purity) pressed",
                "into circular disks with a diameter of 2.0 cm were",
                "bombarded about half an hour. The thickness of sample",
                "was 1.0 mm and 1.3 mm. Each of them was sandwiched",
                "between two monitor aluminum (thin Al foil of 99.99%",
                "purity) foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutrons fluence rate was about 4 E10n/s.",
                "The bombardment for 38.0 min was followed by cooling",
                " (4.7 min) and gamma ray accumlation (10.7 min). Two",
                "samples were placed at 50 and 135 degree angles",
                "relative to the deuterium beam direction and 3.5 cm",
                "far from the T-Ti target."
              ]
            }
          ],
